			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2155')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=36269&amp;TOPIC_ID=4604&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Looking+for+info+about+the+Sleeper&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         -- I heard that the Sleeper is basically the uber dragon of EQ. --<BR>Basically, yes.</P><P>-- That he lives in Velious somewheres. --<BR>He sleeps in Sleeper's Tomb, his actual name is Kerafyrm.</P><P>-- That if you wake him up he rampages through Velious wiping out entire zones then goes back to sleep. --<BR>To wake him up, you have to kill 4 warders (dragons) that usually make sure he won't wake up. Reason being, he has a strong disliking to the other dragons on Velious, and goes to Skyshrine, wiping out everything including Lord Yelinak, and then somehow disappears.</P><P>-- That he has never been killed on any server. --<BR>True. At a Fain Faire, some Verant employee Deathtouched (as in, 20k dmg) the sleeper for 5 or 10 minutes straight (as in, pressing the button continuously) and didn't even move the health bar much, if at all.</P><P>-- That a group of guilds came close(like 25% health left) but were all kicked off by a GM or something for using an exploit to do so. --<BR>No.</P><P>-- That once he is awoken on a given server and gone on his rampage that he can never be awoken on that server again. --<BR>Correct. The warders also stop spawning, depriving said server of some of the best loot in the game (gnome mask &gt; all) :p</P><P>That is also the time when all the EQ message boards get spammed with "OMG they woke sleeper on XYZ_Server they fucked us all wah wah".</P><P>You can still get primal weapons out of ST even without warders, but the other stuff like monk robe, caster mask, and others are gone for good.</P><P>[url=<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=592" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=592</a>]Brother Ronaan[/url]<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
